abstract: Labor Dept reports that weekly unemployment benefits fell 5,000 to seasonally adjusted 271,000, 37th consecutive week that claims held under 300,000.
lead_paragraph: Factory activity picked up slightly in November, too, suggesting that the worst of a manufacturing downturn may be over.

headline.print_headline: Weekly Jobless Claims Fall and Factory Activity Rises
